8
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:46,750
(Summer of 2007)

9
00:01:10,939 --> 00:01:12,109
Hee Seong.

10
00:01:13,879 --> 00:01:15,180
I'm back.

11
00:01:16,579 --> 00:01:19,480
It seemed like you liked
this beer brand,

12
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:21,319
so I took some
without my mom knowing.

13
00:01:24,790 --> 00:01:26,760
Where did you learn to do that?

14
00:01:27,829 --> 00:01:29,459
You said you didn't go to college.

15
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:32,500
Is there an academy
where you learn these things?

16
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:47,280
What are you doing?

17
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:49,450
Can I upload this
on my social media?

18
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:52,879
The caption will be
"My Good-Looking Friend".

19
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:55,489
What are you doing?

20
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,830
Delete it this instant.

21
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:13,370
Okay, I will.

22
00:02:14,669 --> 00:02:15,939
I'll delete it right now.

23
00:02:16,210 --> 00:02:18,280
I didn't know you didn't like
being photographed.

24
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,710
What's your deal?

25
00:02:21,349 --> 00:02:23,520
- What?
- Why are you looking into me?

26
00:02:25,849 --> 00:02:26,889
I did?

27
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:32,490
Do you think I didn't notice
how you looked into me...

28
00:02:32,659 --> 00:02:33,860
so nonchalantly?

29
00:02:34,460 --> 00:02:37,229
You asked about my blood type,
sign, birthday,

30
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,259
and my favorite
and least favorite foods.

31
00:02:40,129 --> 00:02:43,030
You even asked my neighbor
for my number.

32
00:02:44,469 --> 00:02:45,569
What is it?

33
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:47,909
Did someone tell you...

34
00:02:48,539 --> 00:02:49,870
to look into me?

35
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:11,400
I like you.

36
00:03:43,659 --> 00:03:44,759
Hee Seong.

37
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:50,569
Reject, accept, or tell me to wait.

38
00:03:50,569 --> 00:03:52,439
Say something.

39
00:03:54,310 --> 00:03:56,509
- You.
- My name is Cha Ji Won.

40
00:03:59,479 --> 00:04:01,110
Don't you ever come back here.

41
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:04,020
- What?
- Get out right now.

42
00:04:08,849 --> 00:04:11,719
What's wrong?
Do you want me to drag you out?

43
00:05:04,610 --> 00:05:05,810
Why are you already up?

44
00:05:08,610 --> 00:05:10,579
Where did you go at this hour?

45
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:12,149
It's raining.

46
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:14,790
I couldn't sleep,
so I decided to work.

47
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:16,750
Then I ran out of beer.

48
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:21,060
You were worried about having
a beer belly recently.

49
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,399
What?

50
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:26,300
What is it?

51
00:05:27,230 --> 00:05:30,069
Remember when I first confessed
my feelings to you?

52
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,569
You got extremely upset with me.

53
00:05:36,009 --> 00:05:37,839
"Do you want me to drag you out?"

54
00:05:39,579 --> 00:05:41,879
Gosh, why would you bring that up?

55
00:05:43,449 --> 00:05:45,579
Why did you dislike me so much
back then?

56
00:05:48,420 --> 00:05:49,750
It's not that.

57
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:56,160
It was just awkward.
No one confessed to me before.

58
00:05:57,430 --> 00:05:59,800
Look at how innocent you are.

59
00:06:00,629 --> 00:06:02,829
This is why I can't open up
about my past.

60
00:06:03,329 --> 00:06:04,399
Your past?

61
00:06:05,569 --> 00:06:08,209
- Tell me.
- You'll be shocked.

62
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:11,339
- It's that bad?
- I'm a woman with a past.

63
00:06:12,209 --> 00:06:14,110
- I was deceived all along, right?
- Yes.

64
00:06:14,779 --> 00:06:16,810
Tell me. You're making me curious.

65
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:41,009
Does it suit your taste?

66
00:06:46,209 --> 00:06:47,449
I said, does it suit your taste?

67
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,449
I'm not eating this
because it's tasty.

68
00:06:53,649 --> 00:06:54,790
I'm just trying not to die.

69
00:06:56,449 --> 00:06:59,220
Eat up. You will like it.

70
00:07:00,829 --> 00:07:02,730
I bought this near your house.

71
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:08,430
Simply put,
when they perform your autopsy,

72
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,870
they'll find out that this gimbap...

73
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,139
was the last food you ate.

74
00:07:19,709 --> 00:07:21,079
Hyun Su, please.

75
00:07:30,389 --> 00:07:32,660
Hey, what is that?

76
00:07:33,959 --> 00:07:37,959
Are you...
Are you seriously going to kill me?

77
00:07:38,860 --> 00:07:41,129
Is killing someone
that easy for you?

78
00:07:42,329 --> 00:07:43,699
Of course not.

79
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:46,740
How much do you weigh?

80
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:48,839
70kg?

81
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:51,209
75kg?

82
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:55,110
Do you think it'll be easy
to carry you to your car...

83
00:07:55,209 --> 00:07:57,319
when you're all doped up?

84
00:07:57,879 --> 00:08:00,480
Don't do this. Don't.

85
00:08:01,649 --> 00:08:04,920
Hyun Su. Hyun Su, please!

86
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:06,319
Hyun Su...

87
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:17,839
Help! Help me!

88
00:08:18,370 --> 00:08:20,740
I'm in the basement!

89
00:08:22,709 --> 00:08:25,110
I've been kidnapped and confined!

90
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:26,910
He's going to kill me!

91
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,679
Detective Cha!

92
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:36,590
I'm locked down here!

93
00:08:37,019 --> 00:08:39,820
Do Hyun Su, the killer, is here!

94
00:08:42,259 --> 00:08:44,230
He's here!

95
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,659
He's here.

96
00:08:47,399 --> 00:08:49,570
I'm about to go insane.

97
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:54,740
Hey, Hyun Su!

98
00:08:55,269 --> 00:08:57,009
Spare me, will you?

99
00:08:57,909 --> 00:08:59,539
I'll do anything you say.

100
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:02,779
So please spare me.

101
00:09:03,149 --> 00:09:04,779
Please.

102
00:09:04,779 --> 00:09:07,690
Can you answer my question honestly?

103
00:09:07,950 --> 00:09:09,889
Yes. Anything.

104
00:09:16,559 --> 00:09:20,100
In 2011, you wrote this
and uploaded it on the internet.

105
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,399
- What?
- You were still logged in,

106
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:23,399
so I saw this.

107
00:09:28,570 --> 00:09:29,639
Read it.

108
00:09:32,009 --> 00:09:33,139
Read it out loud.

109
00:09:39,580 --> 00:09:43,419
"I'm a female high school student
who's an aspiring screenwriter."

110
00:09:44,889 --> 00:09:48,159
"The person of interest
wasn't aware of a crime..."

111
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:50,429
"and helped out."

112
00:09:52,230 --> 00:09:56,029
"He was recently hired
by a press company."

113
00:09:57,399 --> 00:09:58,799
"What kinds of disadvantages
will he face..."

114
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:00,570
"if his past is revealed?"

115
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:05,080
Keep reading.

116
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:09,750
I said, read.

117
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,190
"And what if..."

118
00:10:19,059 --> 00:10:20,590
"someone had died?"

119
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,700
Is this about you?

120
00:10:31,269 --> 00:10:32,340
No.

121
00:10:33,970 --> 00:10:35,870
(There's a video of the incident.)

122
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:37,210
"There's a video..."

123
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:38,909
"of the incident."

124
00:10:40,309 --> 00:10:42,879
"He just did what was asked of him
without thinking much."

125
00:10:44,379 --> 00:10:45,950
"He really had no idea."

126
00:10:50,519 --> 00:10:51,659
Did you really not know?

127
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:55,860
I didn't know. I didn't know.
I mean it.

128
00:10:56,259 --> 00:10:58,629
This means there's a video...

129
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:01,970
of you assisting murder.

130
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,600
What?

131
00:11:08,539 --> 00:11:09,610
Hyun Su.

132
00:11:10,779 --> 00:11:12,580
I won't tell anyone.

133
00:11:14,649 --> 00:11:17,450
I'll forget about seeing you.

134
00:11:18,879 --> 00:11:20,620
I won't even come near you.

135
00:11:22,049 --> 00:11:23,649
I promise.

136
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:26,019
I'll swear on my mom.

137
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:28,289
So please...

138
00:11:30,529 --> 00:11:33,429
Please let me go.

139
00:11:48,549 --> 00:11:52,179
I want security, not a promise.

140
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,889
I don't trust people's words.

141
00:11:58,090 --> 00:11:59,120
Do you understand?

142
00:12:17,610 --> 00:12:19,809
(Soon Gil Chinese Restaurant)

143
00:12:22,980 --> 00:12:24,679
It's a murder case.

144
00:12:24,850 --> 00:12:26,750
- "A murder case"? Who died?
- What happened?

145
00:12:26,919 --> 00:12:29,019
Mr. Nam,
the owner of the Chinese restaurant.

146
00:12:29,149 --> 00:12:30,889
- I don't know.
- Excuse me.

147
00:12:31,059 --> 00:12:32,259
Excuse us.

148
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:39,529
- Just a second.
- Okay.

149
00:12:58,179 --> 00:12:59,350
(Yeonju Serial Murder Case)

150
00:13:02,789 --> 00:13:03,950
Impossible.

151
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,019
What about his nails?

152
00:13:06,419 --> 00:13:08,259
Have you seen his thumbnails?

153
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:12,299
Both of them are missing.

154
00:13:59,779 --> 00:14:00,779
What is this?

155
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,809
Why is it Do Min Seok again?

156
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:06,519
Is it another disguise
just like Park Seo Young?

157
00:14:09,090 --> 00:14:10,850
Why are you all keeping quiet?

158
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:12,259
This is different
from the Park Seo Young case.

159
00:14:12,759 --> 00:14:13,820
How so?

160
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:17,629
The brand and the color of the leash
Do Min Seok used...

161
00:14:17,629 --> 00:14:20,259
in 2012 on his victims weren't
released to the media or the public.

162
00:14:20,259 --> 00:14:21,269
But...

163
00:14:25,070 --> 00:14:27,970
In this case, the criminal used
the exact same product...

164
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:30,409
Do Min Seok did.

165
00:14:30,509 --> 00:14:32,379
Park Seo Young killed on impulse.

166
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:35,610
On the other hand, this case
was recorded on a security camera.

167
00:14:36,149 --> 00:14:37,549
The murderer planned for it.

168
00:14:38,279 --> 00:14:41,049
Also, he showed how close he is
to Do Min Seok,

169
00:14:41,519 --> 00:14:44,120
and how different he is
from Park Seo Young.

170
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:46,690
He's someone extremely dangerous.

171
00:14:47,389 --> 00:14:50,429
For your record, Do Min Seok
killed seven people.

172
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:53,129
Do you mean...

173
00:14:54,059 --> 00:14:57,100
this could be a serial murder case?

174
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,070
Should we transfer the case
to the regional investigation unit?

175
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:08,750
Section Chief Yoon.
What do you think?

176
00:15:09,179 --> 00:15:11,750
It'd be too good to pass over.
He's always on the front page.

177
00:15:12,350 --> 00:15:14,990
It's not like a serial murder case
already happened.

178
00:15:17,659 --> 00:15:20,360
Woo Chul,
do you think you can handle it?

179
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:27,899
What if it grows into a serial
murder case as we're working on it?

180
00:15:29,029 --> 00:15:31,269
I think we can catch him.

181
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:36,110
The way he picks his victims
is rather rash.

182
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:39,940
Victim Nam Soon Gil was
a built middle-aged man...

183
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:43,350
who lived a routined life
between his work and family.

184
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:47,450
From a criminal's perspective,
he's too risky to kill.

185
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:52,289
I'm sure there's room
for us to dig into.

186
00:15:58,399 --> 00:16:00,330
What does the victim's
family tree look like?

187
00:16:00,629 --> 00:16:03,970
Just a minute. Let's see.

188
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,740
- Ho Joon.
- Yes?

189
00:16:05,940 --> 00:16:09,539
If this becomes a serial murder
case, Captain Lee will lose his job.

190
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:10,669
Let's do a good job.

191
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:12,940
- He must be so anxious.
- Okay.

192
00:16:14,379 --> 00:16:15,909
Nam Soon Gil was an orphan,

193
00:16:15,909 --> 00:16:18,019
so he doesn't have
any families or relatives.

194
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,279
But he has a spouse.

195
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,289
She's currently six months pregnant.

196
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:24,250
She fainted due to the shock
and is resting at a hospital.

197
00:16:24,490 --> 00:16:26,759
Have you figured out who
he talked to on the phone last?

198
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,659
Detective Oh is looking into it.

199
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:34,470
I've identified the last person
Nam Soon Gil talked to on the phone.

200
00:16:34,769 --> 00:16:37,070
It was Kim Mu Jin. He's a reporter
of a weekly publication.

201
00:16:37,399 --> 00:16:38,700
Reporter Kim Mu Jin?

202
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:41,169
Do you know him?

203
00:16:41,509 --> 00:16:43,909
Yes. I met him last Sunday night.

204
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,080
He was writing an article
on Kim Sang Jin's case.

205
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:49,179
Kim Mu Jin can't be reached
right now. His phone's off too.

206
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:52,850
He made his last call yesterday
around 5pm.

207
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:53,980
The person he called...

208
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:56,190
was the victim, Nam Soon Gil.

209
00:17:02,259 --> 00:17:03,389
What are you doing?

210
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:05,400
Detective Choi,
go to the control center...

211
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,130
to analyze
the criminal's escape route.

212
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,500
The two of you need to hurry up
and find Kim Mu Jin's whereabouts.

213
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,869
- Hurry.
- Yes, sir.

214
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:01,049
(Best Reporter of the Month Award)

215
00:18:05,289 --> 00:18:07,619
There's a laptop on the desk
in the living room.

216
00:18:13,599 --> 00:18:14,900
The password...

217
00:18:15,769 --> 00:18:17,500
is "MJ0905".

218
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:23,140
There should be a program
called "S Folder".

219
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:24,480
(Will you allow this app
to make changes to this device?)

220
00:18:24,609 --> 00:18:25,880
Run it.

221
00:18:26,910 --> 00:18:29,180
The password is the same
as the laptop.

222
00:18:30,650 --> 00:18:33,819
There should be a folder named "HS".

223
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:37,650
When you unlock it,

224
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:39,319
you'll see a folder that was hidden
on the desktop earlier.

225
00:18:39,319 --> 00:18:41,059
(HS)

226
00:18:41,759 --> 00:18:43,130
If you want,

227
00:18:44,759 --> 00:18:46,960
you can end my life
whenever you want.

228
00:18:56,910 --> 00:19:00,410
(2002: Sejin High School's
24th Drawing Contest)

229
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:05,680
Hey. Stop filming and sit down.

230
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:08,549
Why aren't you drawing?
Come and draw.

231
00:19:09,450 --> 00:19:10,450
Hurry up.

232
00:19:13,619 --> 00:19:16,089
- This is so boring.
- What is this?

233
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:22,970
Reporter Kim Mu Jin missed work
for two days.

234
00:19:22,970 --> 00:19:24,470
Why didn't you report him missing?

235
00:19:24,839 --> 00:19:27,839
All staff come to work on Mondays
because of our editorial meeting.

236
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:29,369
I don't bother making people
come to work...

237
00:19:29,369 --> 00:19:31,170
before our deadline on Thursday.

238
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:34,509
Reporters don't usually
turn their phones off, do they?

239
00:19:35,049 --> 00:19:36,309
It's normal for Mu Jin.

240
00:19:36,309 --> 00:19:38,519
He'd turn off his phone
and go on a trip or something.

241
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:42,190
Hey. I wonder if Reporter Kim...

242
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:44,589
is locked up somewhere.

243
00:19:44,789 --> 00:19:45,920
What do you mean?

244
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:48,559
I mean in his washroom.

245
00:19:49,589 --> 00:19:52,660
He said he got
locked in his washroom before.

246
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:55,930
He might have died
if his mother didn't visit.

247
00:20:05,809 --> 00:20:07,509
Why do you keep on recording videos?

248
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:20,789
What is this place?

249
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:27,660
Ta-da.

250
00:20:28,069 --> 00:20:29,069
This is it.

251
00:20:29,529 --> 00:20:30,630
What is this?

252
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,539
My dad made this place for me
so I could work here.

253
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:38,109
Isn't it awesome?

254
00:20:42,109 --> 00:20:44,849
Mu Jin, stay still.

255
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:49,289
Didn't you say you'd be my model?

256
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,150
You deceived me?

257
00:21:26,589 --> 00:21:27,819
Reporter Kim.

258
00:21:29,359 --> 00:21:30,529
Are you inside?

259
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:32,559
Reporter Kim?

260
00:21:33,799 --> 00:21:34,799
(Good Food Morning Lunch Box)

261
00:21:40,970 --> 00:21:42,039
There are two.

262
00:21:42,539 --> 00:21:44,640
That means he didn't come home
since Monday afternoon...

263
00:21:45,079 --> 00:21:46,410
or he's trapped inside.

264
00:21:47,339 --> 00:21:48,680
Let's break it open.

265
00:21:49,150 --> 00:21:50,210
Okay.

266
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:56,289
- Please check thoroughly.
- Okay.

267
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:00,259
Reporter Kim?

268
00:22:04,059 --> 00:22:05,230
Reporter Kim?

269
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:15,039
- He's not here.
- No one's home.

270
00:22:16,039 --> 00:22:17,109
He's not here.

271
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:19,079
Where on earth is he?

272
00:22:19,839 --> 00:22:21,910
- You can go now.
- Okay.

273
00:22:23,809 --> 00:22:26,380
(Reporter Kim Mu Jin)

274
00:22:28,490 --> 00:22:30,250
The phone is turned off.
Please leave a message...

275
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:31,349
His phone is turned off.

276
00:22:31,349 --> 00:22:33,589
Shouldn't we consider him
as a missing person?

277
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:51,710
What is it?

278
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:54,880
No one let's new clothes with
a tag on it...

279
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:56,750
get dragged beneath a chair.

280
00:22:57,309 --> 00:22:59,049
Well, I guess so.

281
00:22:59,220 --> 00:23:00,349
Touch this.

282
00:23:03,950 --> 00:23:06,589
- It's warm.
- Someone was here just until now.

283
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:08,829
He might still be here.

284
00:23:09,059 --> 00:23:11,359
The closets, under the bed,
and between the furniture.

285
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:12,730
Let's check one more time.

286
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,319
Ji Won, someone's calling you.

287
00:26:36,769 --> 00:26:37,930
Hey, Hee Seong.

288
00:26:38,339 --> 00:26:41,400
Hey. Do you know a reporter
named Kim Mu Jin?

289
00:26:42,309 --> 00:26:43,470
Reporter Kim Mu Jin?

290
00:26:43,970 --> 00:26:47,740
Yes. He kept saying he knew you.

291
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:52,180
- Do you know him?
- He's at your workshop right now?

292
00:26:53,519 --> 00:26:54,950
What is he doing there?

293
00:26:55,349 --> 00:26:57,849
Honey, can you put him on the phone?

294
00:26:58,390 --> 00:26:59,519
Oh, well...

295
00:27:00,490 --> 00:27:03,230
He said he's charging his phone
in his car and went to get it.

296
00:27:03,660 --> 00:27:05,799
Shall I tell him to call you back?

297
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,900
No, tell him to come to the station.

298
00:27:09,430 --> 00:27:10,529
Okay.

299
00:27:10,829 --> 00:27:13,400
This is urgent, so can you tell him
to come right away?

300
00:27:13,839 --> 00:27:14,940
Sure.

301
00:27:19,539 --> 00:27:22,079
A thief! It's a thief!

302
00:27:22,079 --> 00:27:23,450
It's a thief!

303
00:27:23,450 --> 00:27:25,220
- A thief!
- Wait, I hear something.

304
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,450
Mom, it's a thief!

305
00:27:27,819 --> 00:27:29,420
- Ji Won.
- Yes?

306
00:27:29,619 --> 00:27:31,450
I think I have a fever.

307
00:27:31,990 --> 00:27:33,059
What?

308
00:27:33,589 --> 00:27:35,329
Honey, you need to rest.

309
00:27:35,589 --> 00:27:37,390
Shall I ask my mom
to make some porridge?

310
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:38,400
No.

311
00:27:38,660 --> 00:27:41,160
I'll just take medicine
and get some sleep.

312
00:27:41,900 --> 00:27:44,569
I'm telling you in advance,
since I may not answer the phone.

313
00:27:44,569 --> 00:27:45,640
Okay.

314
00:27:45,940 --> 00:27:48,269
- Ji Won, let's go.
- Okay.

315
00:27:54,039 --> 00:27:56,809
- What is it? What's wrong?
- There's a thief up there.

316
00:27:59,019 --> 00:28:00,049
There's no one there.

317
00:28:00,220 --> 00:28:01,750
But I saw someone up there
just now.

318
00:28:35,650 --> 00:28:37,319
Detective Choi, look at this.

319
00:28:39,359 --> 00:28:41,259
This is an alley right next to
the crime scene...

320
00:28:41,259 --> 00:28:43,029
right after the incident occurred.

321
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:46,160
(Hwesin-dong CCTV)

322
00:28:47,900 --> 00:28:49,029
I got you.

323
00:29:01,140 --> 00:29:04,009
(Where the Morning Star Hovers)

324
00:30:02,769 --> 00:30:03,809
Let go!

325
00:30:07,880 --> 00:30:10,650
Let me go, you scumbag!

326
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,500
I should go home.

327
00:30:29,130 --> 00:30:30,900
- What?
- He's sick.

328
00:30:31,130 --> 00:30:32,869
I should check on him.

329
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:36,109
He's not a kid.
He'll take medication...

330
00:30:36,109 --> 00:30:37,569
or go to the hospital.

331
00:30:37,569 --> 00:30:39,839
It won't take long.
Can you drop me off over there?

332
00:30:40,210 --> 00:30:42,210
Hello, is this
Mr. Park Gyung Chun?

333
00:30:42,710 --> 00:30:44,650
Hello,
I'm Detective Choi Jae Seop...

334
00:30:44,650 --> 00:30:45,880
from Gangsu Police Station's
violent crimes unit.

335
00:30:46,220 --> 00:30:48,650
Didn't you pick up
a customer in a raincoat...

336
00:30:48,650 --> 00:30:51,349
in Hwesin-dong at around 3:30am?

337
00:30:52,119 --> 00:30:54,519
You're a very important testifier.

338
00:30:55,990 --> 00:30:57,289
Goodness, thank you.

339
00:30:57,289 --> 00:30:59,730
Once you arrive, give me a call.

340
00:31:00,630 --> 00:31:01,660
I'm back.

341
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:05,640
Where's Reporter Kim?

342
00:31:05,839 --> 00:31:08,470
What are you talking about?
Weren't you looking for him?

343
00:31:09,410 --> 00:31:10,569
He's not here?

344
00:31:15,279 --> 00:31:17,309
- Hello.
- Hello.

345
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:20,549
The workshop's closed again.
Is your husband okay?

346
00:31:20,619 --> 00:31:22,420
He often closes his workshop
these days.

347
00:31:23,789 --> 00:31:25,619
- He does?
- Yes.

348
00:31:26,089 --> 00:31:27,559
- I'll come back next time.
- Okay.

349
00:31:48,779 --> 00:31:49,910
What's wrong with your face?

350
00:31:50,410 --> 00:31:53,180
Oh, something happened.
It's nothing serious.

351
00:31:53,779 --> 00:31:56,049
- What do you mean?
- Detective Cha.

352
00:31:56,619 --> 00:31:57,890
Weren't we meeting at the station?

353
00:31:58,289 --> 00:32:00,059
What is this?
Are you here to pick me up?

354
00:32:21,539 --> 00:32:22,710
Hey.

355
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:26,420
Do you think
you'll get away with this?

356
00:32:27,319 --> 00:32:29,920
- How dare you deceive me?
- Just kill me.

357
00:32:30,390 --> 00:32:33,059
Go on. Kill me!

358
00:32:34,819 --> 00:32:36,390
I'm a reporter.

359
00:32:36,559 --> 00:32:39,230
I'm not on the same level
as a village foreman.

360
00:32:48,569 --> 00:32:49,670
I can't kill you.

361
00:32:51,869 --> 00:32:53,380
The police are looking for you.

362
00:33:02,950 --> 00:33:04,089
They are?

363
00:33:05,150 --> 00:33:07,859
- Why?
- I don't know the details.

364
00:33:09,690 --> 00:33:10,930
So...

365
00:33:12,259 --> 00:33:14,099
you need to head there right now.

366
00:33:15,769 --> 00:33:19,269
Tidy your hair and wash off
that blood on your wrists.

367
00:33:27,809 --> 00:33:30,950
So the tables have been turned.

368
00:33:31,549 --> 00:33:32,650
Is that right?

369
00:33:34,180 --> 00:33:37,490
Hey, why should I listen to you?

370
00:33:38,490 --> 00:33:40,420
I guess you forgot.

371
00:33:40,859 --> 00:33:42,630
But up until just now,
you were going to kill me,

372
00:33:42,890 --> 00:33:44,359
you psychopath.

373
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:52,769
First, I'd like to hear...

374
00:33:53,039 --> 00:33:56,269
a polite and sincere apology.

375
00:34:04,750 --> 00:34:05,950
There's no time.

376
00:34:13,219 --> 00:34:15,019
If I go to the station right now,

377
00:34:15,559 --> 00:34:18,659
I'll be dying
to put you behind bars.

378
00:34:25,070 --> 00:34:26,739
About that camcorder...

379
00:34:30,670 --> 00:34:31,769
It was quite interesting.

380
00:34:39,179 --> 00:34:40,179
What?

381
00:34:47,690 --> 00:34:49,659
I'm sure it's somewhere.

382
00:34:51,559 --> 00:34:53,230
It's just not in his laptop.

383
00:35:34,139 --> 00:35:35,670
This is amazing.

384
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:40,440
Mu Jin, we need to check
and leave soon. Time's ticking.

385
00:35:42,849 --> 00:35:44,550
My dad will kill me
if we get caught.

386
00:35:44,780 --> 00:35:47,449
Hae Su, you look pretty on camera.

387
00:35:47,519 --> 00:35:48,579
Do you want to die?

388
00:35:48,989 --> 00:35:51,119
I told you not to talk casually
to my sister.

389
00:35:51,719 --> 00:35:54,420
Come on, my brother-in-law.
Loosen up, will you?

390
00:35:55,019 --> 00:35:57,889
- Be quiet. Let's go check.
- Gosh, he's so annoying.

391
00:35:58,329 --> 00:36:00,000
Ghosts don't exist.

392
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,530
I swear I heard something.

393
00:36:01,530 --> 00:36:03,900
Tell Mu Jin to go downstairs alone.

394
00:36:05,099 --> 00:36:06,170
You're too scared to do that, right?

395
00:36:06,170 --> 00:36:08,639
Hey, you just wait here.

396
00:36:08,639 --> 00:36:10,539
I'll interview the ghost
and come back.

397
00:36:11,369 --> 00:36:12,480
Watch out.

398
00:36:13,510 --> 00:36:16,449
All right. Reporter Kim, moving in.

399
00:36:16,809 --> 00:36:17,809
Let's go.

400
00:36:24,489 --> 00:36:25,590
What is this?

401
00:36:31,260 --> 00:36:32,460
That's creepy.

402
00:37:02,889 --> 00:37:03,929
Did you watch it?

403
00:37:05,230 --> 00:37:06,730
I'll keep the tape.

404
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:10,599
If I reveal that tape to the world,

405
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:13,940
you'll have to quit your job.

406
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:15,869
Better yet,

407
00:37:17,969 --> 00:37:19,610
you'll have to leave the country.

408
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:26,050
Had you made a different decision
on that day,

409
00:37:28,449 --> 00:37:31,150
the serial murders would've stopped
then and there.

410
00:37:33,619 --> 00:37:35,360
How many more victims
did you create?

411
00:37:42,829 --> 00:37:44,300
You must watch that video often.

412
00:37:47,369 --> 00:37:48,440
What is it?

413
00:37:51,340 --> 00:37:53,679
Do you relive that moment...

414
00:37:55,510 --> 00:37:56,679
and become excited?

415
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:02,789
Do you think I'm a monster like you?

416
00:38:03,420 --> 00:38:04,449
So what will it be?

417
00:38:05,619 --> 00:38:08,420
Will you do as I say?

418
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:12,360
Or shall we destroy
each other's lives?

419
00:38:26,880 --> 00:38:28,210
What do I need to do?

420
00:38:31,449 --> 00:38:32,579
First,

421
00:38:33,550 --> 00:38:36,349
I'd like to hear...

422
00:38:37,150 --> 00:38:39,190
a polite and sincere apology.

423
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:56,369
Don't worry about me. I'm fine.

424
00:39:00,179 --> 00:39:01,539
Reporter Kim.

425
00:39:02,849 --> 00:39:05,110
I said,
there was a plausible reason.

426
00:39:05,719 --> 00:39:07,820
Wait. He will explain everything.

427
00:39:07,820 --> 00:39:10,650
Mr. Kim Mu Jin,
you are under arrest for assault...

428
00:39:10,889 --> 00:39:12,860
in accordance
with Article 206, Clause 1.

429
00:39:12,860 --> 00:39:14,489
Say something, will you?

430
00:39:14,619 --> 00:39:15,789
Ji Won.

431
00:39:16,659 --> 00:39:18,190
We've already talked it out.

432
00:39:18,559 --> 00:39:21,760
And I started it. It's my fault.

433
00:39:22,199 --> 00:39:24,900
I did something wrong
and made him upset.

434
00:39:24,929 --> 00:39:26,670
Don't be ridiculous.

435
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:28,840
At times,
you need to be coldhearted.

436
00:39:29,340 --> 00:39:32,139
He kept asking for a freebie
in return for writing an article,

437
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:33,610
so I got mad.

438
00:39:34,179 --> 00:39:36,510
I had no idea
you two knew each other.

439
00:39:37,679 --> 00:39:39,750
I pushed his shoulder
and told him to leave.

440
00:39:40,019 --> 00:39:41,179
It's my fault.

441
00:39:46,260 --> 00:39:48,159
You just cursed me in your head,
didn't you?

442
00:39:48,559 --> 00:39:50,429
I have a lot to say,

443
00:39:51,329 --> 00:39:52,900
but I have nothing to say.

444
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:57,630
Let me apologize to you
one more time. Sorry, Reporter Kim.

445
00:39:59,599 --> 00:40:00,900
I was too rude.

446
00:40:01,969 --> 00:40:04,070
I would have treated you better...

447
00:40:04,409 --> 00:40:06,010
if I knew
you two were acquaintances.

448
00:40:06,239 --> 00:40:09,679
Gosh. Really.

449
00:40:10,380 --> 00:40:11,849
That's really...

450
00:40:11,980 --> 00:40:15,050
Reporter Kim. He apologized
to you when he was hit.

451
00:40:15,050 --> 00:40:16,849
Shouldn't you apologize to him
for hitting him first?

452
00:40:22,559 --> 00:40:23,659
I'm sorry.

453
00:40:25,860 --> 00:40:27,960
Honey, does it hurt a lot?

454
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:29,800
Let me see your mouth. Open up.

455
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:31,170
Okay. Here.

456
00:40:32,570 --> 00:40:34,400
Why did you come looking for me,
Detective Cha?

457
00:40:36,909 --> 00:40:37,969
Ma'am.

458
00:40:38,639 --> 00:40:39,840
Do you know Nam Soon Gil?

459
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:42,210
Nam Soon Gil
of Soon Gil Chinese Restaurant?

460
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:45,510
He was murdered early this morning.

461
00:40:53,989 --> 00:40:57,230
Yes, Reporter Kim. I'm Nam Soon Gil.

462
00:40:58,889 --> 00:41:01,059
There's something I forgot
to tell you earlier.

463
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:03,929
You'll be interested to hear this.

464
00:41:05,170 --> 00:41:07,000
This is something I heard recently.

465
00:41:08,239 --> 00:41:11,269
Do Hyun Su actually did it
with his father.

466
00:41:12,170 --> 00:41:13,380
I mean, the serial killing.

467
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:16,349
Are you surprised?

468
00:41:17,579 --> 00:41:20,050
I think I was hypersensitive
because I heard this.

469
00:41:22,719 --> 00:41:23,849
(Gimbap)

470
00:41:28,019 --> 00:41:30,760
Please call me anytime
if you want to hear it in detail.

471
00:41:34,530 --> 00:41:35,969
Reporter Kim.

472
00:41:37,630 --> 00:41:39,070
Do... Do Hyun Su.

473
00:41:40,239 --> 00:41:42,400
Do Hyun Su is here!

474
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:45,210
What did I tell you? I told you
he'd come to avenge me!

475
00:41:50,650 --> 00:41:52,280
The victim knows the criminal.

476
00:41:53,250 --> 00:41:54,420
He called him Do Hyun Su.

477
00:41:54,880 --> 00:41:56,150
Who's Do Hyun Su?

478
00:41:56,619 --> 00:41:58,119
I think you know him.

479
00:41:58,650 --> 00:42:01,519
What is this? It looks like
the case will resolve easily.

480
00:42:01,519 --> 00:42:03,659
We just need to catch
that guy named Do Hyun Su.

481
00:42:03,659 --> 00:42:05,929
And Reporter Kim Mu Jin
knows who he is.

482
00:42:06,230 --> 00:42:07,360
Reporter Kim.

483
00:42:09,900 --> 00:42:12,099
- What?
- I said, who is Do Hyun Su?

484
00:42:15,369 --> 00:42:16,769
Yes.

485
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:19,440
Yes...

486
00:42:20,739 --> 00:42:23,510
Have you heard of Do Min Seok?

487
00:42:23,780 --> 00:42:26,750
Do Min Seok of
the Yeonju Serial Murder Case?

488
00:42:26,849 --> 00:42:27,920
Yes.

489
00:42:28,949 --> 00:42:32,590
Do Hyun Su is the son
of the serial killer Do Min Seok.

490
00:42:35,019 --> 00:42:37,929
I wrote an article
about the two of them.

491
00:42:38,690 --> 00:42:41,860
I used to live close to Do Min Seok.

492
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:44,469
Didn't you say Do Hyun Su
killed the village foreman...

493
00:42:44,829 --> 00:42:48,139
and fled town three months
after his father passed away?

494
00:42:49,369 --> 00:42:50,570
Inside Do Hyun Su's bag...

495
00:42:50,570 --> 00:42:52,840
- Detective, did you find something?
- Yes. Yes.

496
00:42:54,179 --> 00:42:55,909
was the weapon that was used
to kill the village foreman.

497
00:42:56,610 --> 00:42:59,380
I believe he's still wanted
because of that case.

498
00:42:59,579 --> 00:43:01,719
Is he still wanted after 18 years?

499
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:04,250
Is this a long-term cold case?

500
00:43:04,690 --> 00:43:08,190
How is he connected to Nam Soon Gil?

501
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:13,099
After reading my article,
Mr. Nam called me...

502
00:43:13,099 --> 00:43:14,929
saying he has something to report.

503
00:43:15,659 --> 00:43:18,269
He told me that for about 3 years
starting from 2002 fall,

504
00:43:18,869 --> 00:43:21,300
the two of them worked together
to deliver Chinese food.

505
00:43:23,940 --> 00:43:25,570
This is all I know.

506
00:43:26,280 --> 00:43:27,380
I mean it.

507
00:43:28,510 --> 00:43:31,750
What did he mean when he said
Do Hyun Su murdered with his father?

508
00:43:33,820 --> 00:43:36,719
That's just an urban myth.

509
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:42,519
After Do Min Seok committed suicide,
this rumor just went around.

510
00:43:42,889 --> 00:43:44,389
Why did such a rumor go around?

511
00:43:45,590 --> 00:43:46,699
Well...

512
00:43:48,429 --> 00:43:50,969
Because Do Hyun Su
was a little strange.

513
00:43:51,429 --> 00:43:53,599
We didn't know
the exact terminology back then,

514
00:43:53,599 --> 00:43:56,070
so we just said he was possessed
by a ghost.

515
00:43:56,070 --> 00:43:57,170
What terminology?

516
00:44:00,139 --> 00:44:01,909
Antisocial personality disorder.

517
00:44:01,909 --> 00:44:03,780
Why? What did he do?

518
00:44:04,309 --> 00:44:07,780
If anyone got on his nerves,

519
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:09,079
he'd avenge them.

520
00:44:09,590 --> 00:44:12,690
At the time, we thought he'd get
better with age, but he's still...

521
00:44:13,019 --> 00:44:14,590
Yes. My goodness.

522
00:44:14,860 --> 00:44:16,030
"At the time"?

523
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:18,159
You sound like you know
how he's like now.

524
00:44:18,730 --> 00:44:20,360
No, no.

525
00:44:20,659 --> 00:44:23,400
I mean I didn't know I'd meet him
again through a murder case...

526
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:27,099
I didn't know I'd hear his news.

527
